"2000-02-04T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "H", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2000/hou19hb1239a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2000-02-04T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "H", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2000/hou19hb1239a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2000-02-04T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "H", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2000/hou19hb1239a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2000-02-04T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "H", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2000/hou19hb1239a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2000-02-04T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "H", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2000/hou19hb1239a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2000-02-04T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "H", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2000/hou19hb1239a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2000-02-22T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "S", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2000/sen30hb1239a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2000-02-22T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "S", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2000/sen30hb1239a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2000-02-22T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "S", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2000/sen30hb1239a.mp3", "start_seconds": 0.0}], "bill_versions": [{"bill_id": 15663, "bill_version_id": 86549, "bill_version": "Introduced", "bill_version_date": "2000-01-20T00:00:00-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to limit the use of mechanical restraints in juvenile correctional facilities. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That chapter 26-11A be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: No agent or employee of the Department of Corrections may use or employ mechanical restraints upon a juvenile committed to the Department of Corrections except: (1) To prevent imminent bodily harm; (2) To transport any juvenile to and from or between facilities; or (3) To transport any juvenile to or from or during court proceedings. 500 copies of this document were printed by the South Dakota Legislative Research Council at a cost of $.021 per page. . Insertions into existing statutes are indicated by underscores. Deletions from existing statutes are indicated by overstrikes."}, {"bill_id": 15663, "bill_version_id": 86548, "bill_version": "House Engrossed", "bill_version_date": "2000-02-04T00:00:00-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to limit the use of mechanical restraints in juvenile correctional facilities. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That chapter 26-11A be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: No agent or employee of the Department of Corrections may use or employ restraints upon a juvenile committed to the Department of Corrections except: (1) To prevent imminent bodily harm; (2) As a precaution against escape or to prevent an escape; (3) To prevent imminent property damages; or (4) When reasonable under emergency circumstances. For purposes of this Act, restraints are handcuffs, legcuffs, restraint belts, and tethers made of fabric, metal, plastic, or leather; restraint boards, restraint chairs, swaddle beds, and mechanisms to secure cuffs to a bed, restraint board, or chair. Section 2. That chapter 26-11A be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: Any juvenile correctional officer shall complete three hours of instruction regarding domestic abuse and domestic violence. The instruction content shall be approved by the corrections commission established in \u00a7 1-15-1.13. Section 3. That chapter 26-11A be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: The Department of Social Services shall reimburse the Department of Corrections for any domestic abuse and domestic violence training as prescribed in section 2 of this Act. The Department of Social Services shall use funding received from the Violence Against Women Act, set out in Title IV of the Violent Crime Control and Law Enforcement Act of 1994. BILL HISTORY 1/21/00 First read in House and referred to committee assignment waived. H.J. 178 1/24/00 Referred to State Affairs. H.J. 206 1/31/00 Scheduled for Committee hearing on this date. 1/31/00 State Affairs Do Pass, Passed, AYES 10, NAYS 3. H.J. 324 2/2/00 House of Representatives Deferred to another day. H.J. 370 2/3/00 House of Representatives Deferred to another day. H.J. 401 2/4/00 Motion to Amend, Passed, AYES 54, NAYS 11. H.J. 424 2/4/00 House of Representatives Do Pass Amended, Passed, AYES 57, NAYS 7. H.J. 425"}, {"bill_id": 15663, "bill_version_id": 86550, "bill_version": "Senate State Affairs Engrossed", "bill_version_date": "2000-02-16T00:00:00-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to limit the use of mechanical restraints in juvenile correctional facilities. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That chapter 26-11A be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: No agent or employee of the Department of Corrections may use or employ restraints upon a juvenile committed to the Department of Corrections except: (1) To prevent imminent bodily harm; (2) As a precaution against escape or to prevent an escape; (3) To prevent imminent property damages; or (4) When reasonable under emergency circumstances. For purposes of this Act, restraints are handcuffs, legcuffs, restraint belts, and tethers made of fabric, metal, plastic, or leather; restraint boards, restraint chairs, swaddle beds, and mechanisms to secure cuffs to a bed, restraint board, or chair. BILL HISTORY 1/21/00 First read in House and referred to committee assignment waived. H.J. 178 1/24/00 Referred to State Affairs. H.J. 206 1/31/00 Scheduled for Committee hearing on this date. 1/31/00 State Affairs Do Pass, Passed, AYES 10, NAYS 3. H.J. 324 2/2/00 House of Representatives Deferred to another day. H.J. 370 2/3/00 House of Representatives Deferred to another day. H.J. 401 2/4/00 Motion to Amend, Passed, AYES 54, NAYS 11. H.J. 424 2/4/00 House of Representatives Do Pass Amended, Passed, AYES 57, NAYS 7. H.J. 425 2/7/00 First read in Senate and referred to State Affairs. S.J. 343 2/16/00 Scheduled for Committee hearing on this date. 2/16/00 State Affairs Do Pass Amended, Passed, AYES 9, NAYS 0. S.J. 520"}, {"bill_id": 15663, "bill_version_id": 86547, "bill_version": "Enrolled", "bill_version_date": "2000-02-23T00:00:00-06:00", "bill_text": ""}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 15663, "action_date": "2000-01-21T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 85636, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/85636.pdf", "status_text": "First read in House and referred to", "journal_page": 178, "committee_id_action": 656, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 15663, "action_date": "2000-01-24T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 85638, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/85638.pdf", "status_text": "Referred to", "journal_page": 206, "committee_id_action": 656, "committee_id_assigned": 651, "result": "P", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 15663, "action_date": "2000-01-31T19:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 85823, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/85823.pdf", "status_text": "Scheduled for Committee hearing on this date", "journal_page": null, "committee_id_action": 651, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 15663, "action_date": "2000-01-31T19:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 85823, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/85823.pdf", "status_text": "Do Pass,", "journal_page": 324, "committee_id_action": 651, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "P", "vote": {"vote_id": 45681, "president_vote": null, "Yea": [2313, 2333, 2337, 2345, 2351, 2360, 2368, 2388, 2393, 2372], "Nay": [235